        <hl1>'The Change'</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Germaine Greer neglects to mention the true invisibles. They are the women who wouldn't turn heads even at the age of 20. The women who complain the most at reaching 50 are the ones who conquered all by their looks at 20. At menopause the prom queen and the wallflower become equals. The climacteric thus represents the sweet revenge of the plain Jane. ELIZABETH YEW Astoria, Queens</p>
      </block>
